South African Corn, Wheat Falls by Daily Limit in Johannesburg

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-02-23T07:20:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/corn-wheat-prices-fall-by-daily-limits-on-south-africa-s-futures-exchange.html
South African white and yellow corn
futures contracts fell by the daily limit in Johannesburg
trading.  White corn for July delivery, the most active contract,
fell 4.9 percent, or the daily limit of 80 rand ($11.20), to
1,574 rand a metric ton at 9:02 a.m. on the South African
Futures Exchange. Yellow corn was down 4.7 percent, or 80 rand,
at 1,610 per ton.  Wheat for delivery in March fell 3.1 percent, or the daily
limit of 100 rand, to 3,181 rand per metric ton.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mkhululi Mancotywa in Johannesburg at 
 mmancotywa1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
